The paper deals with the problem of domain adaptation in semantic segmentation, specifically in the context of histopathology images. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper proposes a novel network architecture that uses adversarial training to address the domain adaptation problem, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also deals with the problem of spatial inconsistency between domains, which is a common issue in multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
